Bafana Bafana coach Stuart Baxter has confirmed that the National side will play against Zambia, Angola and Zimbabwe during the international break. JOHANNESBURG - Bafana Bafana coach Stuart Baxter has confirmed that the National side will play against Zambia, Angola and Zimbabwe during the international break. Baxter confirmed the fixtures at a media breakfast on Tuesday morning. Bafana will play in a four-nation tournament in Zambia, that will comprise of Angola, Zimbabwe and the hosts. Baxter says that the tournament will serve as preparation for the 2019 Africa Cup of Nations qualifiers in September. Bafana were last in a competitive fixture last November when they played against Senegal in their last World Cup Qualifier. The coach also says that he has been on an extensive trip around Europe where he identified players that are eligible for Bafana selection. The tournament will take place during the March Fifa international window.